record.title: ROOSEVELT CAMPOBELLO INTERNATIONAL PARK COMMISSION

speaking.paragraph: Mr. President, I ask unanimous consent that the Senate proceed to the immediate consideration of Calendar No. 209, S. 1099.

record.chair: The clerk will report the bill by title.
record.narrative: There being no objection, the Senate proceeded to consider the bill.

speaking.paragraph: Mr. President, I ask unanimous consent that the bill be read three times, passed, and the motion to reconsider be laid upon the table; that any statements relating thereto be printed in the Record.

record.chair: Without objection, it is so ordered.
